Never Had such high quality excel course, even in the university. very good !To my taste it lacks a bit of in detail in some of the subjects like:1.How to Select Data source when creating  different charts (Excel got smart but sometimes It doesn't pick the data like you need) ,different charts have different ways selecting the Data source.(which is X-axis and which is the y-axis ?) what is a series ? is it numbers ?including the heading ?It's not even mentioned in the course, How it's like to insert a Blank chart and then assign the data source (very difficult)2. Macros are explained pretty good, how to record, how it works in the background Unfortunately it's only explained for specific actions needed to be automated in the sheetUsing Macros to format sheets isn't explained (how do I do that?),for example:In creating the Dashboard tiles, how do you make a macro to round the edges of all the tiles? do you record doing it for one tile and then apply to whole sheet? to which do you assign the Macro to ?

The Data Visualization in Excel course was incredibly helpful and well-structured. The instructor was knowledgeable and effective in teaching the material, and the exercises provided ample opportunity to put the skills into practice. The course covered a wide range of topics, including creating charts and graphs, using PivotTables and slicers, and building interactive dashboards. I appreciated the emphasis on using real-world data and showcasing creativity, which made the course both engaging and practical. Overall, I highly recommend this course to anyone looking to improve their data visualization skills in Excel.
